on” with NAVS for Classroom Education Project Educating the public about the use of animals in science—and alternatives to their use—is a vital component of NAVS’ mission. Continue reading → April 4, 2016 In Vitro Approach Developed to Study the Blood-Brain Barrier Blood vessels found in the brain play an important role in maintaining what is known as the blood-brain barrier (BBB), a structural and… Continue reading → MORE NEWS ► By the Numbers 155 Current number of sponsors of the Humane Cosmetics Act in the U.S. House of Representatives 16 Number of states (plus Washington DC) with laws or policies allowing students to opt out of classroom dissection exercises 834,453 Number of Animal Welfare Act-covered animals used in research, testing and teaching in the United States in 2014, according to APHIS National Anti-Vivisection Society 53 W. Jackson Blvd., Suite 1552 Chicago, IL 60604 800.888.NAVS (312.427.6065) Privacy Policy | Find Your Legislator | Site Map | Email Us © 2016 National Anti-Vivisection Society
